{
  "sn": "Race to Haven",
  "plot": "DEV: Rance identified attackers as Karsites disguised to implicate Menmellith; theorized prisoners taken for blood magic/ritual sacrifice. Senta and Rance rode non-stop for days; Rance collapsed into Gift-shock sleep for entire journey. Arrived Haven fourth morning; Healers received Rance; Rolan (Queen's Own Companion) met Senta. PEND: Rance's memories of attack still blocked; Gift identity unconfirmed but suspected to be unprecedented power unseen in 500 years; Karsite blood magic revival unverified; Lisle villagers' fate unknown.",
  "entities": [
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Senta",
      "c": "STANCE-Rance: bonded deeply during journey; protective; growing attachment beneath businesslike demeanor; 'you are mine as you are mine'; will knock him unconscious if he loses control (promised). STANCE-Rolan: acknowledged his authority/support but refused to leave Rance's side. STATE: exhausted after days of relentless travel; refused rest to stay with Chosen. Suspects Rance's Gift is rarer/more dangerous than Firestarting—unprecedented power unseen 500 years, no one capable of training it. Confirmed Karsite blood magic is historical fact, not myth; official ban in place for decades but may be returning.",
      "k": ["Senta"]
    },
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Rolan",
      "c": "Queen's Own Companion. Met Senta at Collegium; offered support; told her Rance is in good hands.",
      "k": ["Rolan", "Queen's Own"]
    },
    {
      "t": "lore",
      "n": "Herald-Companion Bond Mechanics",
      "c": "Bond transfers Herald-basics/knowledge naturally to Chosen (Rance knows Empath capabilities, Mind-Healers, protocol without prior training). Companions monitor Chosen's condition through bond continuously. Connection strengthens with time/distance—thoughts and emotions become clearer as minds open to each other. 'Two beings becoming something greater than the sum of their parts.'",
      "k": ["Herald-Companion Bond", "Chosen"]
    },
    {
      "t": "lore",
      "n": "Karsite Blood Magic",
      "c": "Historical practice of capturing people for ritual sacrifice, demon summoning, 'Fires of Vkandis Sunlord' consuming 'impure souls.' Officially banned in Karse for decades. If returning to such practices = major threat implication.",
      "k": ["Karsite Blood Magic", "Karse", "Vkandis Sunlord"]
    }
  ]
}
